<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName LSID="4F9BEE90-F21F-534F-9321-ED901C6DBB50" authority="Westwood, 1868" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Metapelma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metapelma" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Metapelma Westwood, 1868</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="main history of oriental and palaearctic species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Main history of Oriental and Palaearctic species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<bibRefCitation author="Westwood, JO" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" refId="B27" refString="Westwood, JO, 1835. Characters of new genera and species of hymenopterous insects. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 3: 51-54, 68-72." title="Characters of new genera and species of hymenopterous insects. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 3: 51 - 54, 68 - 72." year="1835">Westwood (1835)</bibRefCitation>
established 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Metapelma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metapelma" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Metapelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. spectabile" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="spectabile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. spectabile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Westwood as the type species from North America. 
<bibRefCitation author="Foerster, A" journalOrPublisher="Chalcidiae und Proctotrupii, Aachen" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" refId="B12" refString="Foerster, A, 1856. Hymenopterologische Studien. II. Heft. Chalcidiae und Proctotrupii, Aachen" title="Hymenopterologische Studien. II. Heft." year="1856">
<normalizedToken originalValue="FÃ¶rster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
(1856)
</bibRefCitation>
subsequently described 
<taxonomicName authority="Forster, 1856" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Halidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Halidea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Halidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. nobilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="nobilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">H. nobilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Germany, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Ashmead, WH" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="4 - 20" refId="B1" refString="Ashmead, WH, 1896. On the genera of Eupelminae. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 4: 4 - 20" title="On the genera of Eupelminae." volume="4" year="1896">Ashmead (1896)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Forster, 1856" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Halidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Halidea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Halidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Metapelma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metapelma" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Metapelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4039/entm121149fv" author="Gibson, GAP" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="1 - 121" refId="B14" refString="Gibson, GAP, 1989. Phylogeny and classification of Eupelmidae, with revision of the world genera of Calosotinae and Metapelmatinae (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 149: 1 - 121, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4039/entm121149fv" title="Phylogeny and classification of Eupelmidae, with revision of the world genera of Calosotinae and Metapelmatinae (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea)." url="https://doi.org/10.4039/entm121149fv" volume="149" year="1989">Gibson 1989</bibRefCitation>
for further remarks on generic synonymy).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
Until now, 15 valid extant species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Metapelma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metapelma" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Metapelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Oriental and Palaearctic regions are known, namely 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. albisquamulatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="albisquamulatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. albisquamulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Enderlein from the Philippines, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. beijingense" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="beijingense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. beijingense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from China, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. compressipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="compressipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. compressipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cameron from Malaysia, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. gloriosum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="gloriosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. gloriosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Westwood from the Philippines, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. kokkaricum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="kokkaricum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. kokkaricum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Narendranand &amp; Abhilash from India, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. mesandamna" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="mesandamna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. mesandamna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mani &amp; Kaul from India, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. nobilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="nobilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. nobilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="FÃ¶rster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
) from Germany, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. obscuratum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="obscuratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. obscuratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Westwood from India, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pacificum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="pacificum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. pacificum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nikolskaya from Russia, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. periyaricum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="periyaricum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. periyaricum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Narendranand &amp; Mohana from India, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. rufimanum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="rufimanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. rufimanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Westwood from Malaysia (Sarawak), 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. strychnocola" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="strychnocola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. strychnocola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mani &amp; Kaul from India, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. taprobanae" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="taprobanae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. taprobanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Westwood from Sri Lanka, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. tenuicrus" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="tenuicrus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. tenuicrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gahan from the Philippines, and 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. zhangi" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="zhangi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">M. zhangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Yang from China.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="recognition">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Recognition.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Metapelma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metapelma" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Metapelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of four extant genera described for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kalina" authorityYear="1984" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Neanastatinae">Neanastatinae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1833" family="Eupelmidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="family">Eupelmidae</taxonomicName>
). The genus is differentiated from the other three genera using the keys by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gibson, GAP" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" refId="B15" refString="Gibson, GAP, 1995. Parasitic wasps of the subfamily Eupelminae (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea: Eupelmidae). Memoirs on Entomology International 5: 1-5 + 1-421." title="Parasitic wasps of the subfamily Eupelminae (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea: Eupelmidae). Memoirs on Entomology International 5: 1 - 5 + 1 - 421." year="1995">Gibson (1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.20.161" author="Gibson, GAP" editor="Johnson, N" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="175 - 214" refId="B16" refString="Gibson, GAP, 2009. Description of three new genera and four new species of Neanastatinae (Hymenoptera, Eupelmidae) from Baltic amber, with discussion of their relationships to extant taxa. In: Johnson, N, Ed., Advances in the systematics of Hymenoptera. Festschrift in honour of Lubomir Masner. ZooKeys 20: 175 - 214, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.20.161" title="Description of three new genera and four new species of Neanastatinae (Hymenoptera, Eupelmidae) from Baltic amber, with discussion of their relationships to extant taxa." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.20.161" volume="20" volumeTitle="Advances in the systematics of Hymenoptera. Festschrift in honour of Lubomir Masner." year="2009">2009</bibRefCitation>
), but indivduals can be recognized uniquely by the following combination of characters: head lenticular with short scrobe above each torulus but scrobes not united into a common scrobal depression (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Metapelma beijingense Yang, â, China, Guizhou. A Habitus, dorsal aspect B head, dorsal aspect C head, anterior aspect D antennae, lateral aspect E mesosoma, dorsal aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.926.48688.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/399816" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">3C</figureCitation>
); antenna 13-segmented with flagellum composed of longer than wide anellus, seven funicular segments, and 3-segmented clava (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Metapelma beijingense Yang, â, China, Guizhou. A Habitus, dorsal aspect B head, dorsal aspect C head, anterior aspect D antennae, lateral aspect E mesosoma, dorsal aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.926.48688.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/399816" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">3D</figureCitation>
); scutellum entire, not divided longitudinally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Metapelma beijingense Yang, â, China, Guizhou. A Habitus, dorsal aspect B head, dorsal aspect C head, anterior aspect D antennae, lateral aspect E mesosoma, dorsal aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.926.48688.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/399816" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">3E</figureCitation>
); mesopleuron with upper and lower mesepimeron differentiated posteriorly behind acropleuron (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Metapelma beijingense Yang, â, China, Guizhou. A Head and mesosoma, lateral aspect B metasoma, lateral aspect, C metasoma, dorsal aspect D mid and hind legs, lateral aspect E wings." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.926.48688.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/399817" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">4A, B</figureCitation>
); hind tibia usually conspicuously compressed and widened apically (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Metapelma beijingense Yang, â, China, Guizhou. A Habitus, dorsal aspect B head, dorsal aspect C head, anterior aspect D antennae, lateral aspect E mesosoma, dorsal aspect." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.926.48688.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/399816" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">3A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
